Chelsea and Manchester United are battling it out for Palmeiras wonder kid, Endrick, The Sun reports. Palmeiras record-sale could be on the cards for Endrick this summer, with Chelsea and Man United said to be in the mix. The report added that the likes of Liverpool and Manchester City are also reportedly keen on signing Endrick. They will have to battle Man United and Chelsea for the player’s signature. Endrick, who is one of Palmeiras’ brightest-ever talents, recently turned 16. The Brazilian has now put pen to paper on his first professional deal, a three-year contract. According to transfer expert Fabrizio Romano, Endrick is set to become “one to watch” in the market. Romano tweeted: “Brazilian jewel Endrick turns 16 today and signs new deal with Palmeiras: it will be valid until 2025, including a release clause worth €60m. “There’s already a battle between the European top clubs to sign Endrick. One to watch on the market, soon.”